      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Taking 50,000 IU softgels every other day is still a high dose and not without potential risks. Even if you're feeling symptoms, it's not advisable to self-medicate with such a potent supplement without professional guidance. The body can still accumulate vitamin D, and without knowing your baseline levels or how your body handles the supplement, you could inadvertently cause harm. I strongly recommend speaking with a healthcare provider who can assess your vitamin D status and advise you on the safest and most effective way to address your winter slump. Self-treatment can lead to unintended consequences, and it's always better to be safe than sorry.",
      "source": "target",
